Some additional notes:
@TheBlueMatt [wrote](https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/bitcoin-dev/2021-February/018450.html) on the mailinglist:

> Bitcoin Core does not have infrastructure to handle switching consensus rules with the same datadir - after running with uasf=true for some time, valid blocks will be marked as invalid, and additional development would need to occur to enable s

@TheBlueMatt wrote:
> there's not a good way to test the P2P aspects of a network split

We can now test using binaries of earlier releases, so this might be more feasible. But I'd rather see that in a PR that's specifically focussed on LOT. (my other objections aside)
